-- TABLE-Hong Kong yuan deposits rise 1.6 pct in April vs March
-- By Michelle Chen and Christina Lo
-- Fri May 30, 2014 05:21AM EDT
-- None



May 30 (Reuters) - Yuan deposits in Hong Kong, an offshore market for the Chinese currency, rose to 959.9 billion yuan ($153.83 billion) in April, up 1.6 percent from a month earlier, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority said on Friday.

Cross-border trade settled in yuan fell 23.4 percent in April to 461.5 billion yuan on a month-on-month basis.  The following are yuan deposit data:Hong Kong Deposits:Apr   Mar   Feb   Jan   DecNovYuan (or Rmb bln) 959.9 944.9 920.3 893.4 860.5  827.0   pct change m/m  1.6   2.7   3.0   3.8   4.05.8 pct of total deposits  12.7  12.8  12.3  12.3  12.0   11.7 Total (HK$ bln)   9,392 9,189  9,330 9,184 9,178  9,065Total yuan remittances for cross-border trade settlement (through Hong Kong's banking system):